---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";
---

<Layout title="The vs. Trump Fund.">
  <main>
    <section>
      <h1>vs. Trump Fund</h1>
      <h3>Donate to a portfolio of high-impact campaigns to defeat Trump.</h3>
      <h3>Backed by evidence and vouched for by experts.</h3>
      <h3>
        Weâ€™ve done the research to give you a one-stop-shop to defeat Trump.
      </h3>
      <Button title="Donate Now" />
    </section>

    <section>
      <h1>How it Works</h1>
      <p class="text-center mb-16 -mt-8">
        <em>Your donation is spread across these impactful programs.</em>
      </p>
      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>20%</th>
          <td>Biden campaign</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>15%</th>
          <td
            >Other competitive federal races (the House and Senate are backups
            in case Trump wins)</td
          >
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>30%</th>
          <td
            >The most quantitatively measurable and cost-effective tactics for
            voter registration, persuasion, and turnout.</td
          >
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>25%</th>
          <td
            >Organizations that focus on specific communities and demographics</td
          >
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>10%</th>
          <td>Infrastructure and innovative appropaches</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <p class="mt-16">
        This approach and the organizations we recommend have been vetted by the
        following political experts:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-4">
        <li>David Slifka - Author of Innovation and Money in Politics</li>
        <li>
          Suzi Levine - Political donor advisor and former ambassador to
          Switzerland
        </li>
        <li>Thomas Bates - Professional donor advisor</li>
        <li>Jimmy Hendrix - Author of Giving to Politics Effectively</li>
        <li>Eric Clapton - Professional donor advisor</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <style>
      main {
        margin: auto;
        padding: 1rem;
        width: 800px;
        max-width: calc(100% - 2rem);
        color: #222;
        font-size: 20px;
        line-height: 1.25;
      }
      h1 {
        font-size: 4rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: 1.25;
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 1em;
      }
      h3 {
        font-size: 2rem;
        line-height: 1.25;
        margin-bottom: 1em;
      }
      section {
        padding-top: 4rem;
        padding-bottom: 4rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc;
      }

      /* give me a nice looking table with bold th, nice spacing, lines between */
      table {
        border-collapse: collapse;
        border-spacing: 0;
        width: 100%;
        border: 1px solid #ddd;
      }
      th,
      td {
        text-align: left;
        padding: 16px;
      }
      tr:nth-child(even) {
        background-color: #f2f2f2;
      }
      th {
        background-color: #4caf50;
        color: white;
      }
      td {
        border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
      }
      td:last-child {
        border-bottom: none;
      }
      td:first-child {
        font-weight: bold;
      }

      ul li {
        margin-left: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }
    </style>
  </main>
</Layout>
